{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-tsx","path":"/tutorials/github-pages-and-actions","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>GitHub Pages</h1>\n<p>You can create your custom GitHub Page by creating the following repository: “your-github-name”.github.io, e.g., simonscholz.github.io.\nOnce you created this repository you can simply push an index.html file or whatever webpage content you like to the master branch of the repository.\nThis webpage will then be displayed when hitting “your-github-name”.github.io, e.g., simonscholz.github.io, with your browser.</p>\n<p>This feature is often used to provide a website for the project, which is being hosted on GitHub.\nBut I use this for my personal homepage.</p>\n<p>Also see <a href=\"https://pages.github.com/\">https://pages.github.com/</a> for more information about GitHub pages.</p>\n<p>As you might already guess, this website can be found here: <a href=\"https://github.com/SimonScholz/simonscholz.github.io\">https://github.com/SimonScholz/simonscholz.github.io</a>\nThe source code resides in the <code class=\"language-text\">source</code> branch and the actual site will be automatically build once I push something to the <code class=\"language-text\">source</code> branch.\nAfter that build to build result can be found in the <code class=\"language-text\">master</code> branch.</p>\n<h2>Steps to reproduce</h2>\n<h3>Create the repository</h3>\n<p>Create a new public repository called “your-github-name”.github.io and GitHub will also tell you that this repo is special.</p>\n<h3>Clone the repo and create a source branch</h3>\n<p>Go to your new repository and copy the clone url:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7b31f2663053ad55550def1a85250c47/d93d9/clone-gh-page-repo.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 32.43243243243243%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"clone-gh-page-repo\"\n        title=\"clone-gh-page-repo\"\n        src=\"/static/7b31f2663053ad55550def1a85250c47/fcda8/clone-gh-page-repo.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7b31f2663053ad55550def1a85250c47/12f09/clone-gh-page-repo.png 148w,\n/static/7b31f2663053ad55550def1a85250c47/e4a3f/clone-gh-page-repo.png 295w,\n/static/7b31f2663053ad55550def1a85250c47/fcda8/clone-gh-page-repo.png 590w,\n/static/7b31f2663053ad55550def1a85250c47/efc66/clone-gh-page-repo.png 885w,\n/static/7b31f2663053ad55550def1a85250c47/c83ae/clone-gh-page-repo.png 1180w,\n/static/7b31f2663053ad55550def1a85250c47/d93d9/clone-gh-page-repo.png 1243w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"terminal\"><pre class=\"language-terminal\"><code class=\"language-terminal\">git clone git@github.com:&lt;your-github-name&gt;/&lt;your-github-name&gt;.github.io.git\n\ne.g.\n\ngit clone git@github.com:SimonScholz/simonscholz.github.io.git</code></pre></div>\n<p>Creating the source branch works like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"terminal\"><pre class=\"language-terminal\"><code class=\"language-terminal\">git checkout -b source</code></pre></div>\n<p>In the repository you can setup your website using gatsby.</p>\n<h3>Create a Gatsby starter project</h3>\n<p>As a quick start you can install the <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-cli</code> globally by running:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"terminal\"><pre class=\"language-terminal\"><code class=\"language-terminal\">npm install -g gatsby-cli\n\nor\n\nyarn global add gatsby-cli</code></pre></div>\n<p>This assumes that you’ve already installed npm or yarn.</p>\n<p>Then in the repository folder you can create a Gatsby starter project by calling <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby new gatsby-site https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby-starter-hello-world</code> inside your repository.</p>\n<p>Once this is done you can call <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby develop</code> and navigate to <a href=\"http://localhost:8000\">http://localhost:8000</a> to see the page.</p>\n<p>Feel free to modify this starter project or even build a proper page according to your needs.\nYou’ll find plenty of good docs, tutorials and examples on <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/\">https://www.gatsbyjs.com/</a>.</p>\n<h3>Github action to automatically deploy your Gatsby website</h3>\n<p>You already know that the contents of the <code class=\"language-text\">master</code> branch will be used as source for your GitHub Pages website.\nTo avoid building your Gatsby locally by using the <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby build</code> command and pushing the result to the <code class=\"language-text\">master</code> branch over and over again, you can utilize GitHub actions to automate these steps.</p>\n<p>Therefore create a <code class=\"language-text\">./github/workflows</code> folder inside the repo on the source branch, which contains a <code class=\"language-text\">main.yml</code> with the following contents:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"yaml\"><pre class=\"language-yaml\"><code class=\"language-yaml\"><span class=\"token comment\"># Name of the action</span>\n<span class=\"token key atrule\">name</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 🚀 Deploy website\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Controls when the action will run.</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># In this case the actions will be run when pushing to the source branch of your repository</span>\n<span class=\"token key atrule\">on</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"token key atrule\">push</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"token key atrule\">branches</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>source<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># A workflow run is made up of one or more jobs that can run sequentially or in parallel</span>\n<span class=\"token key atrule\">jobs</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\"># This workflow contains a single job called \"build\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token key atrule\">build</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># The type of runner that the job will run on</span>\n    <span class=\"token key atrule\">runs-on</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> ubuntu<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>latest\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\"># Steps represent a sequence of tasks that will be executed as part of the job</span>\n    <span class=\"token key atrule\">steps</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n      <span class=\"token comment\"># Checks-out your repository under $GITHUB_WORKSPACE, so your job can access it</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> <span class=\"token key atrule\">uses</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> actions/checkout@v2\n\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span> <span class=\"token key atrule\">name</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Gatsby Publish\n        <span class=\"token key atrule\">uses</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> enriikke/gatsby<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>gh<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>pages<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>action@v2.1.1\n        <span class=\"token key atrule\">with</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n          <span class=\"token comment\"># A personal access token needed to push your site after it has been built.</span>\n          <span class=\"token key atrule\">access-token</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> $<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> secrets.ACCESS_TOKEN <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n          <span class=\"token comment\"># The branch expected by GitHub to have the static files needed for your site.</span>\n          <span class=\"token key atrule\">deploy-branch</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> master\n          <span class=\"token comment\"># Additional arguments that get passed to `gatsby build`.</span>\n          <span class=\"token key atrule\">gatsby-args</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>verbose</code></pre></div>\n<p>The contents of the <code class=\"language-text\">main.yml</code> file runs the jobs when pushing to the <code class=\"language-text\">source</code> branch.\nFirst the code of the <code class=\"language-text\">source</code> branch will be checked out and thanks to <a href=\"https://github.com/enriikke/gatsby-gh-pages-action\">https://github.com/enriikke/gatsby-gh-pages-action</a> the Gatsby website will be built and then pushed to the master branch.</p>\n<p>Your <code class=\"language-text\">main.yml</code> file can also contain secret variables, like <code class=\"language-text\">${{ secrets.ACCESS_TOKEN }}</code> for providing an access token.</p>\n<h3>Personal access token with push repository rights</h3>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-gh-pages-action</code> needs access to your repository in order to be able to push to the <code class=\"language-text\">master</code> branch.\nPersonal access tokens can be created by navigating here: <a href=\"https://github.com/settings/tokens\">https://github.com/settings/tokens</a> or by using the UI to your accounts <code class=\"language-text\">settings &gt; developer settings &gt; Personal access tokens</code>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/500dbe12df33576db2342367e3d8265c/c211c/personal-access-token.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 37.83783783783784%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"personal access token settings\"\n        title=\"personal access token settings\"\n        src=\"/static/500dbe12df33576db2342367e3d8265c/fcda8/personal-access-token.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/500dbe12df33576db2342367e3d8265c/12f09/personal-access-token.png 148w,\n/static/500dbe12df33576db2342367e3d8265c/e4a3f/personal-access-token.png 295w,\n/static/500dbe12df33576db2342367e3d8265c/fcda8/personal-access-token.png 590w,\n/static/500dbe12df33576db2342367e3d8265c/efc66/personal-access-token.png 885w,\n/static/500dbe12df33576db2342367e3d8265c/c83ae/personal-access-token.png 1180w,\n/static/500dbe12df33576db2342367e3d8265c/c211c/personal-access-token.png 1502w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>After hitting the <code class=\"language-text\">Generate new token</code> button you can enter a note and select proper scopes for the rights granted for the access token.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4c247fee14f25c7a1adcb9a2f576e1c0/23592/generate-access-token.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.67567567567568%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"generate personal access token\"\n        title=\"generate personal access token\"\n        src=\"/static/4c247fee14f25c7a1adcb9a2f576e1c0/fcda8/generate-access-token.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4c247fee14f25c7a1adcb9a2f576e1c0/12f09/generate-access-token.png 148w,\n/static/4c247fee14f25c7a1adcb9a2f576e1c0/e4a3f/generate-access-token.png 295w,\n/static/4c247fee14f25c7a1adcb9a2f576e1c0/fcda8/generate-access-token.png 590w,\n/static/4c247fee14f25c7a1adcb9a2f576e1c0/efc66/generate-access-token.png 885w,\n/static/4c247fee14f25c7a1adcb9a2f576e1c0/23592/generate-access-token.png 1031w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Assuming that the repo is public the <code class=\"language-text\">public_repo</code> scope should be sufficient.</p>\n<p>Then just hit the <code class=\"language-text\">Generate token</code> button and copy the access token.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/20bae05d7fa9cea7bec9b896fb7ea3fc/8ea22/generated-access-token.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 27.7027027027027%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"generated personal access token\"\n        title=\"generated personal access token\"\n        src=\"/static/20bae05d7fa9cea7bec9b896fb7ea3fc/fcda8/generated-access-token.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/20bae05d7fa9cea7bec9b896fb7ea3fc/12f09/generated-access-token.png 148w,\n/static/20bae05d7fa9cea7bec9b896fb7ea3fc/e4a3f/generated-access-token.png 295w,\n/static/20bae05d7fa9cea7bec9b896fb7ea3fc/fcda8/generated-access-token.png 590w,\n/static/20bae05d7fa9cea7bec9b896fb7ea3fc/efc66/generated-access-token.png 885w,\n/static/20bae05d7fa9cea7bec9b896fb7ea3fc/8ea22/generated-access-token.png 1023w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Make sure to copy this token in a save place, because you won’t be able to see it any more after refreshing the page.</p>\n<h3>Using the access token in the build file</h3>\n<p>Instead of directly pasting the generated personal access token into the <code class=\"language-text\">main.yml</code> file, you’d rather save it securely so that nobody can make use of it.\nThat’s where repository secrets come into play.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c53a8a3db0162d8b1d7476c87bc1ca37/7a1fb/repository-secret.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 69.5945945945946%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"repository secret\"\n        title=\"repository secret\"\n        src=\"/static/c53a8a3db0162d8b1d7476c87bc1ca37/fcda8/repository-secret.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c53a8a3db0162d8b1d7476c87bc1ca37/12f09/repository-secret.png 148w,\n/static/c53a8a3db0162d8b1d7476c87bc1ca37/e4a3f/repository-secret.png 295w,\n/static/c53a8a3db0162d8b1d7476c87bc1ca37/fcda8/repository-secret.png 590w,\n/static/c53a8a3db0162d8b1d7476c87bc1ca37/efc66/repository-secret.png 885w,\n/static/c53a8a3db0162d8b1d7476c87bc1ca37/7a1fb/repository-secret.png 1030w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>After clicking on the <code class=\"language-text\">New repository secret</code> button you can give the enter a name and a value.\nTo be compliant with the given <code class=\"language-text\">main.yml</code> file the name should be <code class=\"language-text\">ACCESS_TOKEN</code> and the value has to be the personal access token, which was generated and copied earlier.</p>\n<p>Congrats! After all these steps your Gatsby website will be build automatically when pushing to the source branch and then be deployed to the master branch.</p>","timeToRead":5,"frontmatter":{"date":"November 22, 2020","title":"GitHub Pages with Gatsby built by GitHub Actions","author":"Simon Scholz"}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["2006812849","2917690675"]}